    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "that's a fair point. but i'm worried about the math. if my costs go up significantly because of the wage hike, i'll probably have to raise my prices or cut staff. do economists usually see this as a net positive for local economies, or is the argument that it mostly just hurts the small guys and helps big corporations who can afford to absorb the cost?",
